  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Kalaripayattu is an ancient martial art of India which has been practiced for centuries. It
      is mentioned in Vedic litrature of Ayurveda,Dhanurveda and Yoga. The main elements of
      Kalaripayattu include training in physical, combat, breathing exercises, higher form of
      meditation and specific class of medical treatments. The purpose of the experimental study is
      to determine the effect of kalaripayattu on psychological well-being and behaviour in
      children.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
